reviews.review: Great ending to the Skywalker saga. Great action and payoff for all the things set up during this 9 movie story.
The movie have great moment but the it go wait to fast in is execution. Nice idea poorly executed.

Of course people are seeing it, because it is in fact more "Star Wars", but it's not very good Star Wars, in fact it was downright irritating how bad it was at times, especially a couple of the characters "interactions"...

Not sure why the critic RT score is 57%.  Just got out of the theater. It was great! I saw a complaint from someone else that it was "tied up too neatly" and I'd like to counter with, "It's the end! You'd be pi$$ing and moaning if things weren't tied up and left you with a bunch of unanswered questions.  Hubs (who is a die hard fan) and I really enjoyed it.  I have one small "meh" thing about it, but it's honestly not even worth mentioning and is just a personal preference thing.  Just go see it and enjoy the wild ride.  We are already planning to go see it again after Christmas.
The best of the sequel trilogy. As a Star Wars fan I'm happy to say this is a good conclusion to the saga.

Professional movie critics are like professional weather forecaster, wrong most of the time. The Rise of Skywalker is a strong stand alone movie let alone a movie bearing the weight of original Star Wars Lore. Even better, what some critics view as gaps in the movie, I view as really cool areas the Star Wars universe will ultimately explore! Thank you Skywalkers!

There are times that the plot feels rushed, overly convenient, and almost video game-ish. But for the most part it's a good installment with striking visuals, homages to the originals, strong emotional performances, and enough twists to keep you engaged. It's not the story I would have told, but it holds water as a worthy conclusion to an epic saga.
A big mess, jumps from one pointless plot point to another, tries to cobble together a bunch of fans favourite moments but fails on all of them

This is a situation where critics liked 8 and now 9 has to fix it for people who enjoy Star Wars.  You had to fix it because you can't close this epic thumbing your nose in the face of it like 8.  This felt good...gave me some gutteral reactions...JWilliams is always great...and well was Star Wars.  Fanservice....yes.... should there be....yes.
Not as good as previous. Slow, disjointed story line, tried to tie up loose quick.
